X_1,\cdots X_n
A = \sum_{i=1}^nX_i \geq l
B= \sum_{i=1}^n X_i \geq k
A \circ B = \sum_{i=1}^nX_i \geq l+k
\mathbb{P}(A\circ B)\leq \mathbb{P}(A)\mathbb{P}(B)
S_j = \sum \limits^j  X_i, \tau_l = 
\mathbb P (S_n > k+l) = \sum_i \mathbb P (\tau_l = i) \mathbb P(S_{n-i} > k)
\le \sum \mathbb P (\tau_l = i) \mathbb P(S_n > k)  = $$ \mathbb P(S_n > l) \mathbb P(S_n > k)
